(a) File, sign, verify, and present all pleadings, applications, petitions, and documents on my behalf;

(b) Appear and argue on my behalf before the said Court and all subordinate and appellate courts;

(c) Admit, deny, or compromise any matter or claim in the said proceedings;

(d) Receive notices, orders, and summons on my behalf;

(e) Withdraw or settle the case, if necessary;

(f) File appeals, revisions, or reviews, if necessary;

(g) Generally do all acts, deeds, matters, and things as may be necessary for the proper conduct and prosecution/defense of the said case.

